France is the country that is in the most time zones, after Russia. It has 12 different time zones, which are spread out across its territories and dependencies around the world. These include Metropolitan France (UTC+01:00), French Guiana (UTC−03:00), French Polynesia (UTC−10:00), Guadeloupe (UTC−04:00), Martinique (UTC−04:00), Mayotte (UTC+03:00), New Caledonia (UTC+11:00), Réunion (UTC+04:00), Saint Barthélemy (UTC−04:00), Saint Martin (UTC−04:00), Saint Pierre and Miquelon (UTC−03:00), and Wallis and Futuna (UTC+12:00).